title: For Sale:  Winchester Large Rifle Primers
postcontent: For sale. 3 boxes of 1,000 and 1/2 box 500  Winchester Large Rifle Primers:Total of 3,500.  These primers will work on rifle brass that has a large primer pocket. Not suggested for using in brass that is going to be fired though any semi automatic rifles that have floating firing pins. Not suggested for reloading MAGNUM rifle brass.       The reason for selling these primers. I purchased these primers for reloading 7.62x39 brass to be fired through my AK-47.Supposedly these primers are okay for this application.        I knew to check this.The AK-47 has a floating firing pin. The firing pin will strike the round following a fired round, through testing 3 of these rounds had a dimple on the primer face.     I have switched over to CCI#200 Primers,these primers are thicker and harder. With the CCI #200 Primers  the round following a fired round, the primer face has a slight indication that the floating firing pin hit it, no dimple.    I fired 20 rounds having one round in the chamber and one round in the magazine,using the Winchester primers in my AK-47,I never had a slam fire. I don't take chances,when I can see a dimple on the primer of 3 not fired rounds.      No shipping because the cost of the required HAZMAT FEE, would not make it economically feasible.I Will sell individual boxes of 1,000 Primers and the 500 Primers that are not in the original box of 1,000. It's 20.00 per box of 1,000. $10.00 for the 500 Primers or $60.00 for all of them.
